{"updated_at": "2012-03-15T12:38:54Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-03-15T12:38:54Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4518703", "id": 4518703, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5448", "issue_id": 5448, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/JonRowe", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "d79fc498d7a5b2ce12180890247476f0", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d79fc498d7a5b2ce12180890247476f0?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F4ae1dff9b97cae45d75aa55942d3d2d4.png", "id": 162976, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/events{/privacy}", "login": "JonRowe", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonRowe/followers"}, "body": "Shouldn't happen as long as comma's are escaped. So confirm.\r\n\r\nTimeout seems to use thread, but neither thread nor timeout catch the hanging on MRI ruby. It seems Dir.glob goes straight into C and blocks somewhere low down in Ruby, beyond the reach of the thread scheduler / GIL\r\n\r\nMy theory is that without escaping you are essentially globing the entirety of the filesystem, if you leave an unpatched version going long enough on OS X you get access denied errors for various private system directories bubbling up.", "_id": {"$oid": "523817e8bd3543c15100dfdb"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5448#issuecomment-4518703"}
